x4freetext: The spectrometer consisted of a l2.7-cm diam.
by 5.l-cm thick crystal of NaI(TI) mounted on a
DuMont K-1198 photomultiplier tube.
KI(Tl) scintillation detector served as a
monitor by counting protons from the D(d,p)T companion
reaction
Cross sections were obtained by measuring the total
number of counts per neutron under each photoabsorption
peak
Correction for attenuation of both neutrons
and gamma rays in the converter.
